g point: the presence of false news – similar to current fake news – in ancient Greek literature, especially in tragedy and historiography when it comes to the use of the derivatives of ἄγγελος.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aLiteratur Griechisch. 4aNachrichten. 4aTransmission.  aTidings.  alegacy.  atransmission.  aἄγγελος.0 cEPUBz97831110229560 cprintz978311102166940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311102237640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111022376423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111022376/original  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK